# DedgeAuth Ecosystem Architecture

Full architecture docs with Mermaid diagrams: `C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\docs\DedgeAuth-Ecosystem-Architecture.md`

## IIS Topology (all apps under Default Web Site, port 80)

| Path | App | ApiPort |
|---|---|---|
| `/DedgeAuth` | Auth server (DedgeAuth.Api) | 8100 |
| `/DocView` | Document viewer | 8282 |
| `/GenericLogHandler` | Log aggregation | 8110 |
| `/ServerMonitorDashboard` | Server monitoring | 8998 |
| `/AutoDocJson` | Documentation tool | 5280 |
| `/AutoDoc` | Static docs | — |

## Auth Code Exchange Flow

1. Unauthenticated user → `DedgeAuthRedirectMiddleware` → `/DedgeAuth/login.html?returnUrl=...`
2. Login at DedgeAuth → JWT + short-lived auth code
3. Redirect back with `?code=<authCode>`
4. `DedgeAuthTokenExtractionMiddleware` exchanges code server-to-server → JWT stored in cookie
5. `DedgeAuthSessionValidationMiddleware` validates via `GET /api/auth/validate` (cached 30s)
6. On validation, fires-and-forgets `POST /api/visits/record` for visit tracking

## Consumer App Integration (3 lines)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddDedgeAuth(builder.Configuration);  // services
app.UseDedgeAuth();                                     // middleware
app.MapDedgeAuthProxy();                                // proxy endpoints
```

Do NOT call `UseAuthentication()`/`UseAuthorization()` separately.

